AN ACT relating to financial administration; providing that any
money remaining in the Grant Matching Account at the
end of the fiscal year does not revert to the State General
Fund; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Nevada Grant Matching Program within the Office of
2 Federal Assistance in the Office of the Governor to provide funds as grants to state
3 agencies, local agencies, tribal governments and nonprofit organizations for the
4 purpose of satisfying the matching funds requirement for a federal grant. (NRS
5 223.490) Existing law also: (1) creates the Grant Matching Account as part of the
6 Program; and (2) requires money in the Account, except for money received from a
7 grant, gift or donation to the Account, that has not been committed for expenditure
8 on or before June 30 of an odd-numbered fiscal year to revert to the State General
9 Fund. (NRS 223.492) This bill provides that any money remaining in the Account
10 at the end of a fiscal year does not revert to the State General Fund and requires the
11 balance in the Account to be carried forward to the next fiscal year.
